qx|I3,Follow up bids|ht|b|fp|1|cs|1|cp|4|at|^-{  Follow-Up Bids }
^-|ht|c|FP||cs||cp||AT|^B@2^*BMM: ^*NAfter partner opens the bidding with 1@C or 1@D and you bid 3@C or 3@D respectively the rebid by opener is simple. In most instances he bids pass and the partnership plays in a partscore. On occasions, opener has a huge hand and can bid 3N with other suits stopped or game in minor bid.|
PG| ***** 31 ***** |


AT|

However, if the bidding goes 1@C-P-2@C-P or 1@D-P-2@D-P the partnership starts bidding the cheapest full-stoppers in the other three suits up the line. The first partner who is assured that the three suits are stopped bids either 2NT or 3NT based on his hand's strength. This can happen with opener's first rebid assuming he has all the requirements to do so. On the other hand, the partnership stops at partscore in the bid minor if they are lacking full stopper in one of the suits.|
PG| ***** 32 ***** |


AT|

First we deal with when both partner have full stoppers. Let us look at a few examples.|
PG| ***** 33 ***** |


