The search for a safe NT contract begins after a single raise by responder. Opener should bid his lowest stopper up the line. Responder keeps the bidding open by bidding the next stopper. Either, opener or responder can bid NT in the appropriate level when all suits are stopped. If not either can retreat to the bid minor. |
